<PB REF="00000214.tif" N="128"></L>
<L>Hadde we &thorn;e dragoun wonne,</L>
<L>We hadde &thorn;e feireste pris vnder sonne!'<NOTE PLACE="foot">2745 f.:<Q><L><I>[(Boldeliche we schole (B. we wyl</I> SN; <I>We schall b.</I> C) <I>to (tyl</I> S) <I>hym [Boldely to hym we shall</I> M] <I>goo</I></L><L><I>And</I> (om. SN) <I>&thorn;orw&yogh; (wyth</I> C) <I>&thorn;e</I> (om. SN) <I>(grace off god (we shul</I> add. SN) <I>hym sloo.</I></L></Q> ESNCM.<Q><L><I>Sere B. (&thorn;edyrward began to (forthe can</I> C) <I>ryde</I></L><L><I>And Ascopard (by hys syde (can abyde</I> C).</L></Q> add. EC.</NOTE></L>
<L>Ascopard swor, be sein Ion,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="2571"></L>
<L N="2748">A fot ne dorste he for&thorn;er gon.</L>
<L>Beues answerde and seide &thorn;o:<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>answede</I> (!) A.</NOTE></L>
<L>'Ascopard, whi seistow so?<NOTE PLACE="foot">2747&mdash;2750:<Q><L><I>'Nay (Then</I> C; <I>sir</I> add. N) <I>for so&thorn;e,' quod (seyde</I> CM) <I>Ascopard,</I></L><L><I>'I wole (turne a&yogh;en (a&yogh;eyn</I> SM; <I>go home</I> N; <I>go</I> C) <I>homward (ayenward</I> N):</L><L><I>I nolde (ne wolde</I> NM; <I>wolde not</I> C) <I>ffor al he&thorn;enysse</I></L><L><I>Haue (a sy&yogh;te off hym (of him a sight</I> SNM), <I>iwysse!'</I></L><L><I>(&THORN;oo seyde</I> (<I>'Ascaparte,' quod</I> M) <I>sere</I> (om. CM) <I>B. (swythe</I> add. C) <I>&thorn;an:</I></L><L><I>'I wende, (&thorn;at</I> add. C) <I>&thorn;ou were (had be</I> M. <I>(a dou&yogh;ty (an hardy</I> EM) <I>man:</I> ESNCM)</L></Q></NOTE></L>
<L>Whi schelt &thorn;ow afered be<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="2575"><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Whi sch.] Wilt</I> SNCM; <I>Woldyst</I> E. <I>&thorn;ow] so</I> add. SNCM. <I>af.] now</I> add. E.</NOTE></L>
<L N="2752">Of &thorn;ing &thorn;at &thorn;ow mi&yogh;t nou&yogh;t sen?'<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Of] For</I> S; <I>a</I> add. EC. <I>&thorn;at] ar</I> EC. <I>maiste not</I> M; <I>hym</I> E; <I>hyt</I> C; <I>neuer</I> SN.</NOTE></L>
<L>A swor, alse he moste &thorn;en,</L>
<L>He nolde him nei&thorn;er hire ne sen:</L>
<L>'Icham weri, ich mot haue reste;</L>
<L N="2756">Go now for&thorn; and do &thorn;e beste!'</L>
<L>&THORN;anne seide Beues &thorn;is wordes fre:</L>
<L>'Schame hit is, to terne a&yogh;e!'</L>
<L>A smot his stede be &thorn;e side,</L>
<L N="2760">A&yogh;en &thorn;e dragoun he gan ride,</L>
<L>&THORN;e dragoun se&yogh;, &thorn;at he cam<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="2585"></L>
<L>&YOGH;enande a&yogh;enes him anan,</L>
<L>&YOGH;enande &amp; gapande on him so,</L>
<L N="2764">Ase he wolde him swolwe &thorn;o.</L>
<L>Whan Beues se&yogh; &thorn;at ilche si&yogh;t,</L>
<L>&THORN;e dragoun of so meche mi&yogh;t,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="2590"></L>
<L>Hadde &thorn;er&thorn;e opnede anon,</L>
<L>For drede a wolde &thorn;er in han gon;</L>
<L N="2769">A spere he let to him glide</L>
<L>And smot &thorn;e dragoun on &thorn;e side;</L>
<L>&THORN;e spere sterte a&yogh;en anon,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="2595"></L>
<L N="2772">So &thorn;e hail vpon &thorn;e ston,</L>
<L>And to-barst on pices fiue.<MILESTONE UNIT="A folio" N="190b:2"></L>
<L>His swerd he drou&yogh; alse bliue;
<PB REF="00000215.tif" N="129"></L>
<L>&THORN;o &thorn;ai fou&yogh;te, alse i &yogh;ow sai,</L>
<L N="2776">Til it was hi&yogh; noun of &thorn;e dai.</L>
<L>&THORN;e dragoun was atened stronge,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="2601"></L>
<L>&THORN;at o man him scholde stonde so longe;</L>
<L>&THORN;e dragoun harde him gan asaile</L>
<L N="2780">And smot his hors wi&thorn; &thorn;e taile</L>
<L>Ri&yogh;t amideward &thorn;e hed,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="2605"></L>
<L>&THORN;at he fel to grounde ded.</L>
<L>Now is Beues to grounde brou&yogh;t,</L>
<L>Helpe him god, &thorn;at alle &thorn;ing wrou&yogh;t!</L>
<L>Beues was hardi and of gode hert,</L>
<L>A&yogh;en &thorn;e dragoun anon a stert<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="2610"></L>
<L>And harde him a gan asaile,</L>
<L N="2788">And he a&yogh;en wi&thorn; strong bataile;</L>
<L>So be-twene hem leste &thorn;at fi&yogh;t,</L>
<L>Til it was &thorn;e &thorn;erke ni&yogh;t.</L>
<L>Beues hadde &thorn;anne swich &thorn;rast,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="2615"></L>
<L N="2792">Him &thorn;ou&yogh;te, his herte to-brast;</L>
<L>&THORN;anne se&yogh; he a water him be side,</L>
<L>So hit mi&yogh;te wel be-tide,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="2618"></L>
<L>Fain a wolde &thorn;eder flen,</L>
<L N="2796">He ne dorste fro &thorn;e dragoun ten;</L>
<L>&THORN;e dragoun asailede him fot hot,</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; is taile on his scheld a smot,</L>
<L>&THORN;at hit cleuede heuene ato,</L>
<L N="2800">His left scholder dede also.</L>
<L>Beues was hardi &amp; of gode hert,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="2625"></L>
<L>Into &thorn;e welle anon a stert.<NOTE PLACE="foot">After <I>anon</I> follows <I>a lep,</I> expuncted.</NOTE></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Lordinges, herkne&thorn; to me now:</L>
<L>&THORN;e welle was of swich vertu:</L>
<L N="2805">A virgine wonede in &thorn;at londe,</L>
<L>Hadde ba&thorn;ede &thorn;er in, ich vnderstonde;</L>
<L>&THORN;at water was so holi,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="2631"></L>
<L N="2808">&THORN;at &thorn;e dragoun, sikerli,</L>
<L>Ne dorste ne&yogh;e &thorn;e welle aboute</L>
<L>Be fourti fote, saundoute.</L>
<L>Whan Beues parseuede &thorn;is,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="2635"></L>
<L N="2812">Wel glad a was in hertte, i-wis;</L>
<L>A dede of is helm of stel</L>
<L>And colede him &thorn;er in fraiche wel,</L>
<L>And of is helm a drank &thorn;ore</L>
<L N="2816">A large galon o&thorn;er more.</L>
<L>A nemenede sein Gorge, our leuedi kni&yogh;t,<MILESTONE UNIT="A folio" N="191a:1"><MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="2641"></L>
<L>And sete on his helm, &thorn;at was bri&yogh;t;
<PB REF="00000216.tif" N="130"></L>
<L>And Beues wi&thorn; eger mode</L>
<L N="2820">Out of &thorn;e welle sone a &yogh;ode;</L>
<L>&THORN;e dragoun harde him asaile gan,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="2645"></L>
<L>He him defende&thorn; ase a man.</L>
<L>So be-twene hem leste &thorn;e fi&yogh;t,</L>
<L N="2824">Til hit sprong &thorn;e dai li&yogh;t.</L>
<L>Whan Beues mi&yogh;te aboute sen,</L>
<L>Bli&thorn;e he gan &thorn;anne ben;<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="2650"></L>
<L>Beues on &thorn;e dragoun hew,</L>
<L N="2828">&THORN;e dragoun on him venim &thorn;rew;</L>
<L>Al ferde Beues bodi &thorn;ere,</L>
<L>A foule mesel alse &yogh;if a were;</L>
<L>&THORN;ar &thorn;e venim on him felle,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="2655"></L>
<L N="2832">His flesch gan ranclen &amp; tebelle,</L>
<L>&THORN;ar &thorn;e venim was icast,</L>
<L>His armes gan al to-brast;</L>
<L>Al to-brosten is ventaile,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="2659"></L>
<L>And of his hauberk a &thorn;osend maile.</L>
<L N="2837">&THORN;anne Beues, sone an hi&yogh;e</L>
<L>Wel loude he gan to Iesu cri&yogh;e:</L>
<L>'Lord, &thorn;at rerede &thorn;e Lazaroun,</L>
<L N="2840">Diliure me fro &thorn;is fend dragoun!'</L>
<L>&THORN;o he se&yogh; his hauberk toren,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="2665"></L>
<L>'Lord!' a seide, '&thorn;at I was boren!'</L>
<L>&THORN;at seide Beues, &thorn;ar a stod,</L>
<L N="2844">And leide on, ase he wer wod;</L>
<L>&THORN;e dragoun harde him gan asaile</L>
<L>&amp; smot on &thorn;e helm wi&thorn; is taile,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="2670"></L>
<L>&THORN;at his helm cleuede ato,</L>
<L N="2848">And his bacinet dede also.</L>
<L>Tweies a ros and tweies a fel,</L>
<L>&THORN;e &thorn;redde tim ouer-&thorn;rew in &thorn;e wel;</L>
<L>&THORN;ar inne a lai vp ri&yogh;t,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="2675"></L>
<L>A neste, wha&thorn;er hit was dai o&thorn;er ni&yogh;t.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>o&thorn;er] &thorn;e</I> A.</NOTE></L>
<L N="2853">Whan ouer-gon was his smerte</L>
<L>And rekeured was of is hertte,</L>
<L>Beues set him vp anon;</L>
<L N="2856">&THORN;e venim was awei igon,</L>
<L>He was ase hol a man,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="2681"></L>
<L>Ase he was, whan he &thorn;eder cam.</L>
<L>On is knes he gan to falle,</L>
<L N="2860">To Iesu Crist he gan to calle:</L>
<L>'Help,' a seide, 'godes sone,<MILESTONE UNIT="A folio" N="191a:2"></L>
<L>&THORN;at &thorn;is dragoun wer ouer-come!<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="2686"></L>
<L>Boute ich mowe &thorn;e dragoun slon,</L>
<L N="2864">Er &thorn;an ich hennes gon,
<PB REF="00000217.tif" N="131"></L>
<L>Schel hit neuer aslawe be</L>
<L>For noman in cristente!'<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="2690"></L>
<L>To god he made his praiere</L>
<L N="2868">And to Marie, his moder dere;</L>
<L>&THORN;at herde &thorn;e dragoun, &thorn;er a stod,</L>
<L>And fle&yogh; awei, ase he wer wod.</L>
<L>Beues ran after, wi&thorn; outen faile,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="2695"></L>
<L N="2872">And &thorn;e dragoun he gan asaile;</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; is swerd, &thorn;at he out braide,</L>
<L>On &thorn;e dragoun wel hard a laide,</L>
<L>And so harde a hew him &thorn;an,</L>
<L>A karf ato his heued pan,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="2700"></L>
<L>And hondred dentes a smot &thorn;at stonde,</L>
<L N="2878">Er he mi&yogh;te keuren a wonde,</L>
<L>A hitte him so on &thorn;e cholle</L>
<L N="2880">And karf ato &thorn;e &thorn;rote bolle.</L>
<L>&THORN;e dragoun lai on is side,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="2705"></L>
<L>On him a &yogh;enede swi&thorn;e wide.</L>
<L>Beues &thorn;anne wi&thorn; strokes smerte</L>
<L N="2884">Smot &thorn;e dragoun to &thorn;e herte,</L>
<L>An hondred dentes a smot in on,</L>
<L>Er &thorn;e heued wolde fro &thorn;e bodi gon,</L>
<L>And &thorn;e gode kni&yogh;t Beuoun<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="2711"></L>
<L N="2888">&THORN;e tonge karf of &thorn;e dragoun;</L>
<L>Vpon &thorn;e tronsoun of is spere</L>
<L>&THORN;e tonge a stikede for to bere.</L>
<L>A wente &thorn;o wi&thorn; outen ensoine<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="2715"></L>
<L N="2892">To-ward &thorn;e toun of Coloine.</L>
<L>&THORN;anne herde he belles ringe,</L>
<L>Prestes, clerkes loude singe;</L>
<L>A man &thorn;er he ha&thorn; imet,</L>
<L>And swi&thorn;e faire he ha&thorn; him gret,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="2720"></L>
<L N="2897">&amp; asked &thorn;at ilche man &thorn;o,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;at] at</I> (!) A.</NOTE></L>
<L>Whi &thorn;ai ronge &amp; songe so.</L>
<L>'Sire,' a seide, 'wi&thorn; outen faile,</L>
<L N="2900">Beues is ded in bataile;</L>
<L>&THORN;ar fore, for so&thorn;e I saie &thorn;e:<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="2725"></L>
<L>Hit is Beues dirige!'</L>
<L>'Nai,' que&thorn; Beues, 'be sein Martin!'</L>
<L N="2904">And wente to bischop Florentin.</L>
<L>&THORN;o &thorn;e bischop hadde of him a si&yogh;t,<MILESTONE UNIT="A folio" N="191b:1"></L>
<L>A &thorn;ankede Iesu ful of mi&yogh;t<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="2730"></L>
<L>And brou&yogh;te Beues in to &thorn;e toun</L>
<L N="2908">Wi&thorn; a faire prosesioun;
<PB REF="00000218.tif" N="132"></L>
<L>&THORN;anne al &thorn;e folk &thorn;at &thorn;ar was,</L>
<L N="2910">&THORN;ankede Iesu of &thorn;at gras.<NOTE PLACE="foot">2753&mdash;2910:<Q><L><I>Ascopard sayde wi&thorn; reweful chere:</I><MILESTONE UNIT="E folio" N="141a"><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>I kepe no&yogh;t (nodur</I> C) <I>him (to</I> add. C) <I>se ne (nor</I> C) <I>here</I> NC; <I>I kepe no&yogh;t to see him in no manere</I> S.; <I>Me &thorn;ynke, it is a lowthly bere, &THORN;e deuyl of hell &thorn;au&yogh; hit were.</I> add. SN.</NOTE></L><L><I>'Fare weel, ffor I wole nou&yogh;t come &thorn;ere!'</I><NOTE PLACE="foot">1 f. om. M.</NOTE></L><L><I>Sere B. sayde anon ry&yogh;t &thorn;oo:</I><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Sere]</I> om. C. <I>ry&yogh;t]</I> om. C. <I>&THORN;an seide (bespake</I> M) <I>sir B. &thorn;o</I> SNM.</NOTE></L><L><I>'I wole hym see, ar &thorn;at I goo!</I><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>wole] shal</I> SNM. <I>&thorn;at I] I</I> M; <I>y hennes</I> SN.</NOTE></L><L N="5"><I>I hope, now I see hym here,</I></L><L><I>Me &thorn;ynki&thorn;, I here a reweful chere!'</I><NOTE PLACE="foot">5 f. om. SNCM.</NOTE></L><L><I>&THORN;anne prekyd sere B. hys steede,</I><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>sere]</I> om. M. <I>syr Befyse prekyd</I> C. <I>steede] be side</I> add. M.</NOTE></L><L><I>To &thorn;e dragoun he gan to rede.</I><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ri&yogh;t to</I> SN; <I>And to</I> M. <I>to]</I> om. M. <I>he&mdash;rede] forth he &yogh;ede</I> SN; <I>a well gode spede</I> C.</NOTE></L><L><I>Whanne &thorn;at ffoule cursyd dragoun</I><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And when</I> C. <I>&thorn;at] the</I> CM; <I>ilke</I> add. SN. <I>ffoule]</I> om. M. <I>cursyd]</I> om. SNCM. <I>drag.] nere was</I> add. M.</NOTE></L><L N="10"><I>Hadde a sy&yogh;te off sere Beffoun,</I><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And had</I> M. <I>Beues</I> M.</NOTE></L><L><I>He gan casten vp a &yogh;elle,</I><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>gan] to</I> add. SNM. <I>gan c.] caste</I> C. <I>cast vp a] crye and (to</I> add. N) SN.</NOTE></L><L><I>Men my&yogh;ten heren hym in to helle.</I><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Men&mdash;hym] His voys was herde</I> SN;