<L>And Miles wi&thorn; gret cheualry;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>wi&thorn; g. ch.] his brother hardely</I> SN; <I>that was hardy</I> C.<Q><L><I>Tyrryes son, &thorn;at hight Beuoun,</I></L><L><I>A</I> (om. N) <I>&yogh;ong kny&yogh;t (kny&yogh;tis</I> N) <I>and hardy in felde and toun.</I></L></Q> add. SN.<Q><L><I>And syr Tarryes sone, &thorn;at hy&yogh;t Befown,</I></L><L><I>They went to gedur owt of &thorn;e towne.</I></L></Q> add. C.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;ai come to Saber at &thorn;at stour<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>When &thorn;ey</I> SN; <I>Tyll &thorn;ey</I> C. <I>Saber at]</I> om. SNC. <I>&thorn;at] hard</I> add. SN.</NOTE><MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="3915"></L>
<L N="4096">And brou&yogh;te Saber gode sokour<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And br. S.] Saber &thorn;ei brou&yogh;t</I> SN.</NOTE></L>
