<L>Fram prime til vnderne gan to ringe.</L>
<L N="4169">Alle, &thorn;at si&yogh;en hem wi&thorn; si&yogh;t,</L>
<L>Seide, neuer in none fi&yogh;t<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="3990"></L>
<L>So stronge bataile si&yogh;e er &thorn;an</L>
<L N="4172">Of Sarasin ne of cristene man.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>At hi&yogh; midday &thorn;e king Iuore,</L>
<L>To Beues he smot a dent ful sore,</L>
<L>&THORN;at sercle of gold &amp; is crestel<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="3995"></L>
<L N="4176">Fer in to &thorn;e mede fel.</L>
<L>Doun of &thorn;e helm &thorn;e swerd gan glace</L>
<L>And karf ri&yogh;t doun be-fore is face,</L>
<L>Doun ri&yogh;t &thorn;e viser wi&thorn; is swerd</L>
<L>And half &thorn;e her vpon is berd.<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4000"></L>
<L>Ac &thorn;our&yogh; &thorn;e help of godes grace<MILESTONE UNIT="A folio" N="198b:2"></L>
<L>His flesch no&thorn;ing atamed nas.</L>
<L>&THORN;o cride &thorn;e Sarasins al at ones:</L>
<L N="4184">'&THORN;is Beues wi&thorn; his grete bones
<PB REF="00000284.tif" N="198"></L>
<L>Ful sone wor&thorn; imaked tame!'<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4005"></L>
<L>&THORN;o wex Beues in gret grame</L>
<L>And &thorn;ou&yogh;te wel wi&thorn; Morgelay</L>
<L N="4188">&YOGH;elden his strok, &yogh;if &thorn;at he may.</L>
<L>To king Yuor he gan areche</L>
<L>Anon wi&thorn; oute more speche<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4010"></L>
<L>Vpon &thorn;e scholder in &thorn;at tide,</L>
<L N="4192">&THORN;at half a fot hit gan in glide.</L>
<L>For smertte Yuor in &thorn;at stounde</L>
<L>Fel a knes vnto &thorn;e grounde,</L>
<L>Ac vp he sterte in haste &thorn;an<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4015"></L>
<L N="4196">&amp; in wra&thorn;&thorn;e to Beues ran</L>
<L>&amp; &thorn;ou&yogh;te han Beues aqueld;</L>
<L>And Beues keppte him wi&thorn; is scheld,</L>
<L>And Yuore wi&thorn; &thorn;e strok of yre</L>
<L>Made fle in to &thorn;e riuere<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4020"></L>
<L N="4201">A large quarter of his scheld,</L>
<L>&THORN;at neuer nas atamed in feld.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>atamed] d</I> written above the line. A.</NOTE></L>
<L>Or Yuor mi&yogh;te his hond wi&thorn;-drawe,</L>
<L N="4204">Beues, &thorn;e kni&yogh;t of cristene lawe,</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; Morgelay a smot him &thorn;o,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4025"></L>
<L>&THORN;at his scheld he clef ato,</L>
<L>And his left hond, be &thorn;e wrest</L>
<L N="4208">Hit fle&yogh; awei &thorn;our&yogh; help of Crist.</L>
<L>Whan Yuor hadde his hond lore,</L>
<L>He fau&yogh;t, ase he wer wod &thorn;er fore,</L>
<L>And hew to Beues in &thorn;at tide,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4031"></L>
<L N="4212">No strok ne moste o&thorn;er abide.</L>
<L>&THORN;o Beues se&yogh; is strokes large,</L>
<L>He kepte his strokes wi&thorn; is targe;</L>
<L>&THORN;o Beues to Yuor gan flinge<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4035"></L>
<L>And &thorn;our&yogh; &thorn;e mi&yogh;t of heuene king</L>
<L N="4217">His ri&yogh;t arm &amp; is scholder bon</L>
<L>He made fle to gronde anon.</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; &thorn;at strok Yuor &thorn;e Mombraunt</L>
<L>Cride: 'Merci, Teruagaunt,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4040"></L>
<L N="4221">Mahoun, Gouin and Gibiter,</L>
<L>Reseue now me saule her,</L>
<L>For wel ich wot, ich am dede!'</L>
<L>&THORN;o Beues herde him so grede,<MILESTONE UNIT="A folio" N="199a:1"></L>
<L>He seide: 'Yuor, let be &thorn;at cri<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4045"></L>
<L>And clepe to god and to Mari,</L>
<L>And let &thorn;e cristen, er &thorn;e deie,</L>
<L N="4228">Or &thorn;ow schelt go &thorn;e worsse weie</L>
<L>And wi&thorn; outen ende dwelle</L>
<L>In &thorn;e stronge peine of helle!'<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4050"></L>
<L>'Nay,' que&thorn; Yuor, 'so mot y &thorn;en,</L>
<L N="4232">Cristene wile ich neuer ben,</L>
<L>For min is wel &thorn;e beter lawe!'</L>
<L>&THORN;o Beues herde &thorn;at ilche sawe,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4054"></L>
<L>A felde him doun, wi&thorn; outen faile,</L>
<L N="4236">And vnlacede his ventaile,</L>
<L>And tok him be &thorn;e heued anon</L>
<L>And strok hit fro &thorn;e scholder bon,</L>
<L>And on his spere he hit pi&yogh;te.</L>
<L>And &thorn;o &thorn;e cristen si&yogh;e &thorn;at si&yogh;te,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4060"></L>
<L N="4241">&THORN;ai &thorn;ankede god in alle wise,</L>
<L>&THORN;at Beues hadde wonne &thorn;e prise.</L>
<L>&THORN;anne al &thorn;e Sarasins lasse &amp; more,</L>
<L N="4244">&THORN;at was ycome wi&thorn; king Yuore,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>wi&thorn;]</I> added above the line. A.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;ai si&yogh;e her lordes heued arered,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4065"></L>
<L>Sore &thorn;ai weren alle afered;
<PB REF="00000285.tif" N="199"></L>
<L>To-ward Mombraunt &thorn;ei wolde fain,</L>
<L N="4248">Ac Saber made hem terne again,</L>
<L>And sire Beues and sire Terry,</L>
