<L>Help him god, &thorn;at alle &thorn;ing wrou&yogh;t!</L>
<L N="4353">Beues at &thorn;e mete sat,</L>
<L>He be-held and vnder-&yogh;at</L>
<L>Al is fon, &thorn;at were &thorn;er oute;<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4175"></L>
<L>He was afered of &thorn;at route.</L>
<L N="4357">He askede at &thorn;e tauarnere,<MILESTONE UNIT="A folio" N="199b:2"></L>
<L>&THORN;at armede folk, what it were.</L>
<L>And he answerde him at &thorn;at sake:</L>
<L>'&THORN;ai ben y-come, &thorn;e to take!'<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4180"></L>
<L N="4361">Whan Beues herde him speke so,</L>
<L>To a chaumber he gan go,</L>
<L>&THORN;at he hadde se&yogh;e armur inne;</L>
<L>In haste &thorn;e dore he gan vp winne</L>
<L>And armede &thorn;er anon ri&yogh;tes<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4185"></L>
<L N="4366">Bo&thorn;e he and is sex kni&yogh;tes,
<PB REF="00000291.tif" N="205"></L>
<L>And gerte him wi&thorn; a gode brond</L>
<L>And tok a spere in is honde,</L>
<L N="4369">Aboute his nekke a doble scheld:</L>
<L>He was a kni&yogh;t stout and belde.<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4190"></L>
<L>On Arondel a lep &thorn;at tide,</L>
<L>In to &thorn;e strete he gan ride.</L>
<L>&THORN;anne seide &thorn;e stiward to sire Bef:</L>
<L N="4374">'A&yogh;ilt &thorn;e, treitour, &thorn;ow foule &thorn;ef!</L>
<L>&THORN;ow hauest &thorn;e kinges sone islawe,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4195"></L>
<L>&THORN;ow schelt ben hanged &amp; to-drawe!'</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Beues seide: 'Be sein Ion,</L>
<L N="4378">Treitour was y neuer non:</L>
<L>&THORN;at i schel ke&thorn;e hastely,</L>
<L>Er &thorn;an ich wende, sikerly!'<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4200">
<PB REF="00000292.tif" N="206"></L>
<L>A spere Beues let to him glide</L>
<L N="4382">And smot him vnder &thorn;e ri&yogh;t side;</L>
<L>&THORN;our&yogh; is bodi wente &thorn;e dent,</L>
<L>Ded a fel on &thorn;e pauiment.</L>
<L>A sede anon after &thorn;at dint:<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4205"></L>
<L N="4386">'Treitour! now is &thorn;e lif itint:</L>
<L>&THORN;us men schel teche file glotouns,</L>
<L>&THORN;at wile misaie gode barouns!'</L>
<L>&THORN;e folk com wi&thorn; grete route,</L>
<L>Besette Beues al aboute;<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4210"></L>
<L N="4391">Beues and is sex kni&yogh;tes</L>
<L>De-fendede hem wi&thorn; al her mi&yogh;tes,</L>
<L>So &thorn;at in a lite stounde</L>
<L>Fiue hondred &thorn;ai brou&yogh;te te gronde.</L>
<L>Beues prikede for&thorn; to Chepe,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4215"></L>
<L N="4396">&THORN;e folk him folwede al to hepe;</L>
<L>&THORN;our&yogh; Godes lane he wolde han flowe,</L>
<L>Ac sone wi&thorn; in a lite &thorn;rowe</L>
<L>He was be-set in bo&thorn;e side,</L>
<L>&THORN;at fle ne mi&yogh;te he nou&yogh;t &thorn;at tide.<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4220"></L>
<L>&THORN;o com &thorn;er fot-men mani &amp; fale<MILESTONE UNIT="A folio" N="200a:1"></L>
<L>Wi&thorn; grete clobbes &amp; wi&thorn; smale!</L>
<L>Aboute Beues &thorn;ai gonne &thorn;ringe</L>
<L N="4404">And hard on him &thorn;ai gonne dinge.</L>
<L>Al Beues kni&yogh;tes, in &thorn;at stounde<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4225"></L>
<L>&THORN;ar hii were feld to grounde</L>
<L>And al to-hewe flesch &amp; bon:</L>
<L N="4408">&THORN;o was Beues wo be-gon,</L>
<L>For he was on &amp; hii were ded;</L>
<L>For sorwe kou&thorn;e he no red;<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4230">
<PB REF="00000293.tif" N="207"></L>
<L>&THORN;at lane was so narw y-wrou&yogh;t,</L>
<L N="4412">&THORN;at he mi&yogh;te defende him nou&yogh;t,</L>
<L>He ne Arondel, is stede,</L>
<L>Ne mi&yogh;te him terne for non ned&edot;.</L>
<L>To Iesu he made his praiere<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4235"></L>
<L N="4416">And to Marie, is moder dere,</L>
<L>&THORN;at he moste pase wi&thorn; is lif,</L>
<L>To sen is children &amp; is wif.</L>
<L N="4419">Out of &thorn;e lane a wolde ten,</L>
<L>&THORN;e chynes held him faste a&yogh;en.<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4240"></L>
<L>Wi&thorn; is swerd he smot &thorn;e chayne,</L>
<L>&THORN;at hit fel a peces twayne,</L>
<L>And for&thorn; a wente in to Chepe;</L>
<L N="4424">&THORN;e folk him folwede al to hepe,</L>
<L>And al &thorn;ai setten vp a cry:<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4245"></L>
<L>'A&yogh;ilt &thorn;e, Beues, hastely,</L>
<L>A&yogh;ilt &thorn;e, Beues, sone anon,</L>
<L>And elles &thorn;ow schelt &thorn;e lif for-gon!'</L>
<L N="4429">Beues seide: 'Ich &yogh;elde me</L>
<L>To god, &thorn;at sit in trinite!<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4250"></L>
<L>To non o&thorn;er man i nel me &yogh;elde,</L>
<L>While &thorn;at ich mai me wepne welde!'
<PB REF="00000294.tif" N="208"></L>
<L N="4433">Now be-ginne&thorn; &thorn;e grete bataile</L>
<L>Of sire Beues, wi&thorn; outen faile,</L>
<L>&THORN;at he dede a&yogh;enes &thorn;at cite:<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4255"></L>
<L N="4436">&yogh;e &thorn;at wile here, herkne&thorn; to me!</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;is was aboute &thorn;e vnder tide,</L>
<L>&THORN;e cri aros be ech a side</L>
<L N="4439">Bo&thorn;e of lane and of strete;</L>
<L>Aboute him com peple grete,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4260"></L>
<L>Al newe &amp; fresch, wi&thorn; him to fi&yogh;t,</L>
<L>Ac Beues stered him ase gode kni&yogh;t,</L>
<L>So &thorn;at in a lite &thorn;rawe<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>while,</I> struck out, add. A.</NOTE></L>
<L N="4444">Fif &thorn;osend &thorn;ar was islawe</L>
<L>Of &thorn;e strengeste, &thorn;at &thorn;er wore,<MILESTONE UNIT="A folio" N="200a:2"></L>
<L>&THORN;at him hadde &yogh;eue dentes sore;</L>
<L>Ac euer his stede Arondel</L>
<L N="4448">Faste fau&yogh;t wi&thorn; hertte lel,</L>
<L>&THORN;at fourty fote be-hinde &amp; forn</L>
<L>&THORN;e folk he ha&thorn; to grounde i-born.<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4270"></L>
<L>&THORN;us &thorn;at fi&yogh;t leste longe</L>
<L N="4452">Til &thorn;e time of euesonge.</L>
<L>Tidinge <I>com</I> to Potenhi&thorn;e,</L>
<L>To Iosian also swi&thorn;e,</L>
<L>&THORN;at Beues in Londen was islawe<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4275"></L>
<L N="4456">And ibrou&yogh;t of his lif dawe.
<PB REF="00000295.tif" N="209"></L>
<L>Iosian &thorn;anne fel aswowe,</L>
<L>Gij and Miles hire vp drowe</L>
<L>And confortede &thorn;at leuedi bri&yogh;t</L>
<L>Hendeliche wi&thorn; alle her mi&yogh;t,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4280"></L>
<L N="4461">And askede hire, what hire were;</L>
<L>And &yogh;he tolde hem anon &thorn;ere,</L>
<L>How Beues was in Londen slayn</L>
<L N="4464">And his kni&yogh;tes wi&thorn; gret payn:</L>
<L>'Now ke&thorn;e, &yogh;e ben noble kni&yogh;tes,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4285"></L>
<L>And wreke&thorn; &yogh;our fader wi&thorn; &yogh;our mi&yogh;tes!'</L>
<L>Sire Gii and Miles seide &thorn;an</L>
<L N="4468">To here moder Iosian:</L>
<L>'Dame, be him, &thorn;at herwede helle,</L>
<L>We scholle his de&thorn; wel dere selle!'</L>
<L>&THORN;anne sire Miles and sire Gii<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4291"></L>
<L N="4472">Gonne hem arme hasteli</L>
<L>And on here knes set hem doun</L>
<L>And bad her moder benesoun.</L>
<L>Sire Gii lep on a rabit,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4295"></L>
<L N="4476">&THORN;at was meche &amp; no&thorn;ing lite,
<PB REF="00000296.tif" N="210"></L>
<L>And tok a spere in is hond,</L>
<L>Out at &thorn;e halle dore a wond</L>
<L>Toward &thorn;e cite of Londen toun,</L>
<L>And sire Miles wi&thorn; gret randoun<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4300"></L>
<L N="4481">Lep vpon a dromedary,</L>
<L>To prike wolde he nou&yogh;t spary.</L>
<L>Whan &thorn;ai come to Londen gate,</L>
<L N="4484">Mani man &thorn;ai fonde &thorn;er ate,</L>
<L>Wel iarmed to &thorn;e te&thorn;,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4305"></L>
<L>So &thorn;e frensche bok vs se&thorn;,</L>
<L>A&yogh;en &thorn;e children &thorn;ei &yogh;eue bataile,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;ei] &thorn;e</I> (!) A.</NOTE></L>
<L N="4488">&amp; hii a&yogh;en, wi&thorn; outen faile,</L>
<L>And made of hem so clene werk,<MILESTONE UNIT="A folio" N="200b:1"></L>
<L>&THORN;at &thorn;ai neuer spek wi&thorn; prest ne clerk;</L>
<L>And after-ward, ase &yogh;e mai hure,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4311"></L>
<L N="4492">Londegate &thorn;ai sette a fure.
<PB REF="00000297.tif" N="211"></L>
<L>Whan &thorn;ai come, wi&thorn; outen faile,</L>
<L>&THORN;o be-gan a gret bataile<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4314"></L>
<L>Be twene Bowe and Londen ston,</L>
<L N="4496">&THORN;at time stod vs neuer on.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;ar was a Lombard in &thorn;e toun,</L>
<L>&THORN;at was scherewed &amp; feloun;</L>
<L N="4499">He armede him in yrene wede</L>
<L>And lep vpon a sterne stede<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4320"></L>
<L>And rod for&thorn; wi&thorn; gret randoun</L>
<L>And &thorn;ou&yogh;te haue slawe sire Beuoun.</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; an vge masnel</L>
<L N="4504">Beues a hite on &thorn;e helm of stel,</L>
<L>&THORN;at Beues of Hamtoun, veraiment,</L>
<L>Was astoned of &thorn;e dent;<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4326"></L>
<L>What for care and for howe,</L>
<L N="4508">He lenede to his sadelbowe.</L>
<L>&THORN;anne com priken is sone Gii,</L>
<L>To helpe his fader, hastely;<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4330">
<PB REF="00000298.tif" N="212"></L>
<L>Wi&thorn; a swerd drawe in is hond</L>
<L N="4512">To &thorn;at Lombard sone a wond</L>
<L>&amp; smot him so vpon &thorn;e croun,</L>
<L>&THORN;at man and hors he cleuede doun;</L>
<L>&THORN;e poynt fel on &thorn;e pauiment,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4335"></L>
<L N="4516">&THORN;e fur sprong out after &thorn;e dent.</L>
<L>&THORN;anne com ride is bro&thorn;er Mile</L>
<L>Among &thorn;e peple in &thorn;at while;</L>
<L N="4519">Al &thorn;o, &thorn;at a mi&yogh;te reche,</L>
<L>Ne dorste he neuer aske leche,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4340"></L>
<L>For to hele &thorn;er is wonde,</L>
<L>&THORN;at he ne lai ded vpon &thorn;e grounde.</L>
<L>&amp; whan Beues se&yogh; &thorn;at si&yogh;te,</L>
<L N="4524">In hertte he was glad &amp; li&yogh;te</L>
<L>&amp; &thorn;ankede Iesu, our sauiour,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4345"></L>
<L>&THORN;at hadde sent him so gode sokour,
<PB REF="00000299.tif" N="213"></L>
<L>And egerliche, wi&thorn; outen faile,</L>
<L N="4528">&THORN;e grete peple he gan asaile.</L>
<L>So meche folk was slawe &amp; ded,</L>
<L>&THORN;at al Temse was blod red;<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4350"></L>
<L>&THORN;e nombre was, veraiment,</L>
<L N="4532">To and &thorn;retti &thorn;osent.
<PB REF="00000300.tif" N="214"></L>
<L>And also sone so hit was ni&yogh;t,<MILESTONE UNIT="A folio" N="200b:2"></L>
<L>To &thorn;e Ledene halle &thorn;ai wente ri&yogh;t;</L>
<L>A fette Iosian wi&thorn; faire meine<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4355"></L>
<L N="4536">To Londen, to &thorn;at riche cite,</L>
<L>&amp; helde a feste fourtene ni&yogh;t</L>
<L>To al &thorn;at euer come, apli&yogh;t!</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="4539">Tiding com to king Edgar,</L>
<L>&THORN;at Beues hadde his men for-fare;</L>
<L>For is borgeis in is cite</L>
<L>He made del and gret pite</L>
<L>&amp; seide: 'Ichaue leued me lif</L>
<L N="4544">Longe wi&thorn; outen werre &amp; strif,</L>
<L>&amp; now icham so falle in elde,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4365"></L>
<L>&THORN;at i ne may min armes welde:</L>
<L>Twei sones Beues ha&thorn; wi&thorn; him brou&yogh;t,</L>
<L N="4548">&THORN;ar fore hit is in me &thorn;ou&yogh;t,
<PB REF="00000301.tif" N="215"></L>
<L>Miles, his sone, me dou&yogh;ter take,</L>
<L>In &thorn;is maner is pes to make.'<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4370"></L>
<L>&THORN;ai grauntede al wi&thorn; gode entent,</L>
<L N="4552">&amp; king Edgar Beues of-sent,</L>
<L>And sire Saber &amp; sire Gii,</L>
<L>And sire Miles &amp; sire Terry,</L>
<L>&amp; king Edgar Miles gan calle<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4375"></L>
<L N="4556">Be fore his barouns in &thorn;e halle</L>
<L>And &yogh;af him is dou&yogh;ter be &thorn;e honde,</L>
<L>And after is day al Ingelonde,</L>
<L>And pes and loue was maked &thorn;are</L>
<L>Be twene Beues &amp; king Edgare.<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4380"></L>
<L N="4561">&THORN;e maide &amp; Miles wer spused same</L>
<L>In &thorn;e toun of Notinghame.</L>
<L>&YOGH;e wite&thorn; wel, &thorn;ou&yogh; i ne telle &yogh;ow,</L>
<L N="4564">&THORN;e feste was riale inow,</L>
<L>Ase scholde be at swiche a spusing</L>
<L>And at &thorn;e kinges couroning;<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4386"></L>
<L>&THORN;e feste leste fourtene ni&yogh;t</L>
<L N="4568">To al &thorn;at euer come, apli&yogh;t!</L>
<L>And at &thorn;e fourtene ni&yogh;t is ende,</L>
<L>Beues tok leue, hom to wende,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4390">
<PB REF="00000302.tif" N="216"></L>
<L>At king Edgar &amp; at Sabere,</L>
<L N="4572">And Miles, is sone, a lefte here</L>
<L>And kiste and &yogh;af him is blessing,</L>
<L>&amp; wente to Mombraunt, &thorn;er he was king;</L>
<L>And his erldom in Hamte-schire<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4395"></L>
<L N="4576">A &yogh;af to his em Sabere</L>
<L>And schipede at Hamtoun hastely,<MILESTONE UNIT="A folio" N="201a:1"></L>
<L>And wi&thorn; him wente his sone Gii,</L>
<L N="4579">And Terry wi&thorn; is barnage.</L>
<L>&THORN;e wind blew hardde wi&thorn; gret rage</L>
<L>And drof hem in to Ermonie,<MILESTONE UNIT="Turnbull line" N="4401"></L>
<L N="4582">&THORN;ar be-lefte his sone Gii<NOTE PLACE="foot">4313&mdash;4582:<Q><LG TYPE="stanza">
<L><I>For&thorn; &thorn;anne rod sere Beffoun</I><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;anne] him</I> SN. <I>rod] went</I> SNC.</NOTE></L>
<L><I>And took hys in ry&yogh;t in &thorn;e toun.</I><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>ry&yogh;t]</I> om. SNC. <I>&thorn;e] London</I> S.</NOTE></L>
<L><I>Whanne B. set to &thorn;e mete,</I><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>B.] was</I> add. SNC. <I>&thorn;e] hys</I> C; om. S.</NOTE></L>
<L><I>&THORN;e styward ha&thorn; hym nou&yogh;t for&yogh;ete;</I><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>ha&thorn;&mdash;for&yogh;.] &thorn;ou&yogh;t to be awreke</I> SN; <I>thoght hym to bete</I> C.</NOTE></L>
<L N="5"><I>He dede cryen in Lundone toun</I><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And</I> SN. <I>dede] made</I> C; <I>let</I> SN. <I>in] &thorn;orow</I> C.</NOTE></L>
<L><I>Bo&thorn;e to burgeys &amp; to garsoun,</I><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Bo&thorn;e to] &THORN;at euery</I> SN; <I>That &thorn;er was nodur</I> C. <I>&amp; to] and</I> SN; <I>nor</I> C.</NOTE></L>
<L><I>To eche man &thorn;ai my&yogh;te armys bere</I><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>To e. m.]</I> om. SNC. <I>&thorn;at] euer</I> add. SN; <I>my&yogh;t a.] ony armys myght</I> C.</NOTE></L>
<L><I>And hys owne hed iwere,</I><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And] Or</I> SN. <I>And&mdash;hed] But he them schulde</I> C.</NOTE></L>
<L><I>For to taken &thorn;e kynges ffoon,</I><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>For]</I> om. <I>S. ffeloon</I> S.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot">put after 10 SNC.</NOTE></L>
<L N="10"><I>He bad armen hem euerychon.</I><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&THORN;at &thorn;ey shuld be redy anoon</I> SN; <I>And &thorn;at &thorn;ey schulde arme &thorn;em ylkoon</I> C.</NOTE></L>
<L><I>Euery lane &amp; euery strete</I><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>In eu.</I> SNC. <I>&amp;] in</I> NC.</NOTE></L>
<L><I>Weren idrawe wi&thorn; chenys grete;</I><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&THORN;ere were</I> SN; <I>Ther was</I> C. <I>wi&thorn;]</I> om. SNC.</NOTE></L>
<L><I>&yogh;iff &thorn;at B. awey wolde ffleen,</I><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>That yf</I> C. <I>&thorn;at]</I> om. SN. <I>wolde awey</I> SNC.</NOTE></L>
<L><I>&THORN;e cheynys scholde hym holden a&yogh;en.</I><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>wolde</I> C. <I>hold him</I> SNC.</NOTE></L>
</LG><LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="15"><I>Tydyng cam to sere Beffoun</I><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Then tydynges</I> C.</NOTE></L>
<L><I>Of al &thorn;is ylke false tresoun;</I><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;is] that</I> C. <I>ylke]</I> om. SN. <I>false] grete</I> S; <I>fowle</I> N; om. C.</NOTE></L>
<L><I>He dede hym arme swy&thorn;e weel,</I><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>He]</I> (<I>Then</I> add. C) <I>sir B.</I> SNC. <I>did arme him</I> N; <I>armyd hym</I> C. <I>sw.]</I> om. SNC.</NOTE></L>
<L><I>Bo&thorn;e in yryn &amp; eke in steel,</I><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>eke]</I> om. SNC.</NOTE></L>
<L><I>And took hys owne lytyl meyne,</I></L>
